The primary limitation of this report is the reliance on secondary sources, which may not capture the full complexity of the historical context. Additionally, the interpretations of the Gilded Age's impact on freedom can vary among historians, leading to potential biases in the sources consulted. Further research using primary sources and a broader range of academic perspectives would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the era's impact on American notions of freedom.

